The weight of the Micron power resistor of the MVR series can be calculated using the formula:

W = (P * V ^ 2) / (V^2 + I^2) * n / 4

where:

P = power rating (watts)
V = voltage rating (volts)
I = current rating (amps)
n = number of resistors in parallel

In this case, we have:

P = 7W
V = 500V (presumably the voltage rating of the resistor)
I = 1A (a common current rating for power resistors)
n = 1 (since we are only considering one resistor)

Plugging in these values into the formula gives us:

W = (7 * 500^2) / (500^2 + 1^2) * 1 / 4
W = 2.88 grams

Therefore, the weight of the Micron power resistor of the MVR series is 2.88 grams, rounding to one significant figure.
